The office of the President has announced that the end-year Cabinet recess will begin on December 22 and end on January 3.
In a statement dated December 18, Head of Public Service Joseph Kinyua said scheduled presidential engagements will continue uninterrupted.
Mr Kinyua said the calendars of the National Security Council (NSC) and the National Security Council Advisory Committee (NSCAC) will also be observed as planned.



